abstract: The Federal Reserve signaled that it wasn’t close to raising interest rates, saying the economy was still weak.
snippet: The Federal Reserve signaled that it wasn’t close to raising interest rates, saying the economy was still weak.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON  The Federal Reserve signaled on Wednesday it was not close to raising interest rates, saying that the economy remained weak even though the recession appeared to be over.

headline.main: Fed Sees No Need to Raise Interest Rates Soon
headline.print_headline: Fed Signals A Rate Rise Is Far Away
